The paper discusses steganography methods and their security against steganalysis methods. This topic falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also mentions the use of co-occurrence matrix, which is commonly used in image processing and computer vision (cs.MM, cs.CV). The paper proposes an adaptive feature to improve the LSB Matching and LSB Matching Revisited methods, which involves manipulating the data in a way that reduces distortion. This manipulation of data can be seen as a form of information theory (cs.IT). Finally, the paper presents experimental results, which involves analyzing data and drawing conclusions, a task that falls under machine learning and data analysis (cs.LG).
